narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This class is pretty difficult, and requires real work, but it is very rewarding and invaluable if you are serious about training your ear.
yes, it changes the way one thinks about music.

I would definitely recommend this course to any music student. It is much more than a mere component of a theory class; it is a comprehensive study of musicianship through the lens of the atonal relativism of the 20th century, and so extremely relevant to any aspect of musical study.
